### Async Error Handling Patterns

**try/catch with async/await:**

```javascript
async function fetchUser(id) {
  try {
    const res = await fetch(`/api/users/${id}`);
    if (!res.ok) throw new Error(`HTTP ${res.status}`);
    return await res.json();
  } catch (err) {
    console.error('fetchUser failed:', err);
    throw err; // re-throw so caller can handle
  }
}
```

**Promise rejection swallowing — the silent killer:**

```javascript
// WRONG: rejection is swallowed
async function bad() {
  const result = await somePromise().catch(() => {}); // returns undefined silently
  result.doSomething(); // TypeError: Cannot read property of undefined
}

// Better: return a fallback or re-throw
async function better() {
  const result = await somePromise().catch(err => {
    logger.error(err);
    throw err; // propagate
  });
}
```

**unhandledRejection — global safety net:**

```javascript
// Node.js
process.on('unhandledRejection', (reason, promise) => {
  console.error('Unhandled rejection at:', promise, 'reason:', reason);
  process.exit(1); // recommended: crash and let process manager restart
});

// Browser
window.addEventListener('unhandledrejection', (event) => {
  console.error('Unhandled:', event.reason);
  event.preventDefault(); // suppress default console error
});
```

**Custom Error subclasses:**

```javascript
class AppError extends Error {
  constructor(message, code, statusCode = 500) {
    super(message);
    this.name = 'AppError';
    this.code = code;
    this.statusCode = statusCode;
    // Fix prototype chain in transpiled environments
    Object.setPrototypeOf(this, AppError.prototype);
  }
}

class NotFoundError extends AppError {
  constructor(resource) {
    super(`${resource} not found`, 'NOT_FOUND', 404);
    this.name = 'NotFoundError';
    Object.setPrototypeOf(this, NotFoundError.prototype);
  }
}

// Usage
try {
  throw new NotFoundError('User');
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof NotFoundError) {
    res.status(err.statusCode).json({ error: err.message });
  }
}
```

**Common trap:** Forgetting `Object.setPrototypeOf` in custom Error subclasses when targeting ES5 via TypeScript/Babel — `instanceof` checks break without it.

**Частая ошибка:** Забыть `Object.setPrototypeOf` в пользовательских подклассах Error при компиляции в ES5 через TypeScript/Babel — проверки `instanceof` ломаются без этого.

